Vice President Kamala Harris met with President Hichilema of Zambia to congratulate him and the Zambian people on a historic election with high voter turnout, particularly among young voters. The meeting focused on shared values between the U.S. and Zambia, and both leaders agreed to collaborate on important issues such as health, pandemic response, good governance, and the rule of law. Harris praised Hichilema's efforts to prioritize reforms and stabilize the Zambian economy. The Vice President also welcomed the establishment of new partnerships to strengthen the bilateral relationship between the U.S. and Zambia.